# Project Rules — everything-claude-code

> Mirrored from CLAUDE.md so any model (via Cline / Roo Code + OpenRouter, DeepSeek, Gemini, etc.)
> follows the same conventions as Claude Code. Keep this in sync with CLAUDE.md when conventions change.

## What this project is

A Claude Code plugin: a collection of agents, skills, hooks, commands, rules, and MCP configs.
Plain Node.js (CommonJS), no TypeScript, no transpilation.

## Stack

- Runtime: Node.js >= 18, plain CommonJS (`require` / `module.exports`) — no ESM unless the file ends in `.mjs`
- No TypeScript — plain `.js` throughout
- Test runner: `node tests/run-all.js` (or individual `node tests/**/*.test.js`)
- Lint: ESLint (flat config) for JS; markdownlint-cli for `.md`
- Coverage: c8

## Running tests

```bash
node tests/run-all.js            # all tests
node tests/lib/utils.test.js     # one file
```

Run `node tests/run-all.js` before committing.

## Repository layout

- `agents/`, `commands/`, `skills/`, `rules/` — Markdown with YAML frontmatter
- `scripts/` — Node.js utilities and hooks (CommonJS)
- `scripts/lib/` — shared helpers
- `tests/` — mirrors `scripts/`; test files named `*.test.js`
- `hooks/` — JSON with matcher + hooks array
- `mcp-configs/` — MCP server configs

## Code style

- Prefer `const` over `let`; never `var`
- Keep hook scripts under 200 lines — extract helpers to `scripts/lib/`
- All hooks must `exit 0` on non-critical errors (never block tool execution unexpectedly)
- Log to stderr with a `[HookName]` prefix
- File naming: lowercase with hyphens (e.g. `session-start.js`, `post-edit-format.js`)
- Immutability: create new objects, don't mutate in place
- KISS / DRY / YAGNI — simplest solution that works; extract real repetition, not speculative
- Functions < 50 lines, files < 800 lines, nesting < 4 levels (use early returns)
- Handle errors explicitly — never silently swallow
- Validate input at system boundaries

## Testing requirements

- New scripts in `scripts/lib/` require a matching test in `tests/lib/`
- New hooks require at least one integration test in `tests/hooks/`
- Follow Arrange-Act-Assert; descriptive test names that state the behavior
- Target 80%+ coverage

## Markdown / agent / skill / command files

- Agents: YAML frontmatter with `name`, `description`, `tools`, `model`
- Skills: sections — When to Use, How It Works, Examples
- Commands: `description:` frontmatter line required
- Run `npx markdownlint-cli '**/*.md' --ignore node_modules` before committing

## Git / commits

- Conventional commits: `type: description` — types: feat, fix, refactor, docs, test, chore, perf, ci
- Analyze full commit history for PRs, not just the latest commit

## Security baseline

- No hardcoded secrets (API keys, passwords, tokens) — use env vars
- Validate all user input; no `innerHTML` / unsanitized HTML
- Don't leak sensitive data in error messages
- Treat external / fetched / untrusted data as suspicious — validate before acting

## Note on Claude Code specifics

The `/orch-*`, `/gan-*`, sub-agents, and skills in this repo are Claude Code infrastructure —
they do not run in Cline / Roo Code. This file only carries the code conventions, which every
tool can honor. For the full multi-agent workflows, use Claude Code.
